HEADWORD: benzocaine
<hw>benzocaine</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a chemical substance obtainable
as a white crystalline ester (<chform>H2N.C6H4.CO.O.C2H5</chform>) used
as a local anesthetic. Chemically, it is <chname>4-aminobenzoic acid
ethyl ester</chname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ethyl p-aminobenzoate.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

